    "4461272": {
      "title": "Dynamically Reconfigurable Complex Emulsions via Tunable Interfacial Tensions",
      "abstract": "Emulsions are of critical importance for research and for applications in the medical sciences, food industry and elsewhere. This paper describes a one-step method that exploits the temperature-sensitive miscibility of hydrocarbon, silicone and fluorocarbon liquids to make three- and four-phase complex emulsions with highly controllable morphologies. The geometry of the emulsions can be accurately tuned between encapsulated and Janus configurations by varying the balance of interfacial tensions controlled through mixtures of surfactant or by stimuli such as light or pH. The ability to reversibly 'present' and 'hide' specific liquidliquid interfaces within the droplet and tune the droplet morphology offers interesting practical possibilities."
